ll medal tallies at the Paris Games.\", \"from\": 1653, \"to\": 1744, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1653, \"end\": 1660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998747513653696, \"rank\": 0.00012497072423352443, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a fresh record\", \"from\": 1676, \"to\": 1690}, {\"ngram\": \"terms\", \"from\": 1694, \"to\": 1699}, {\"ngram\": \"overall medal tallies\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1724}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 1728, \"to\": 1743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Following the exploits of McCarthy and O'Donovan, Harrington, Philip Doyle and Daire Lynch (rowing bronze) and Daniel Wiffen (800m swimming gold), Ireland are already up to five medals and currently 13th in the overall 2024 table.\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1976, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1772, \"end\": 1780, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"score\": 0.8343526472395112, \"rank\": 0.19446214573867313, \"text\": \"McCarthy\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brandon_McCarthy\"}, {\"begin\": 1808, \"end\": 1820, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\", \"score\": 0.809412548681283, \"rank\": 0.22437673130189478, \"text\": \"Philip Doyle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philip_Doyle_(American_football)\"}, {\"begin\": 1893, \"end\": 1900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9998747513653696, \"rank\": 0.00012497072423352443, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_